agicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=325.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Chain casting, XP, focus items and &quot;best&quot; pet</span><hr size=1> Many questions here, so here goes:<br>
First of all, exactly what level do focus items actually start to add the &quot;mystery % to stats&quot;? I've read as low as level 4, then 29 and 34. I never bothered to get my focus items until 29, since that is supposedly when they start working. Reclaim energy works at 29, but Im still not sure about it making a stronger pet yet (to lazy to test this). Also, when I was a lower level mage, I would do what most (smart players) would do when summoning a pet: summon till you get either an even or yellow con pet. Well, once we hit level 20 (I think its 20), we no longer get pets up to or past our level. So how can you tell what the &quot;best&quot; pet is, once you have reached your new spell level? Its easy when your one level away from new spells, because you summon many light blue (high green) pets until you get a blue, but before then, all I get is &quot;he looks quite fomidable&quot; and thats it. So I cant tell any diff when I summon pets level 22-26 until I raise in levels myself and get closer to 34.....<br>
Next, when it comes to chain casting, I understand that /pet get lost erases the hate list of the mob for exp purposes...but, what happens if you /pet get lost when a mob is only at 1/4 life and then you chain another pet on it? If your new pet finishes off the 1/4 life, does that count as the current pet doing 100% of the mobs total life (if you didnt nuke), thereby giving you 50% exp? Im sure its not hard doing /pet get lost when the mob only has 1/10 its hp, and then just nuking once, but it will probably take practice getting a mob low enough to finish it with just ONE nuke, without accidentally having the pet kill it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udarkclawthedarkavenger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkclaw The Dark Avenger</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(11/24/01 7:14:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=325.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jaddesign.com/esrbm.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Chain casting, XP, focus items and &quot;best&quot; pet</span><hr size=1> Well, I remember at lvl 16 when me and another friend were hunting in Oasis.<br>
<br>
He summoned a fire pet with a focus item, I summoned a normal fire pet. His pet was bigger than mine, so if pet got bigger at lvl 16 I would think the focus items start working at lvl 16.<br>
<br>
How to know if your pets the best it can be past lvl 20?? Simple, ask someone 3+ lvls higher than you to con your pet. If pet cons BLUE to that person then its a good pet, if it's anything below BLUE (light blue/green) then you can summon a better one. <br>
<br>
Also at lvl 39+ you can see what pet you have simply by looking at how much pet is hitting for. Example, if your lvl 44 pet hits for 44, then it's 2 lvls below his max (max is when you use FOCUS ITEM). If you use focus item and you get a pet that hits for 46, then your pet is one lvl below his max. If you summon a pet that hits for 48, that's the max. Same thing at lvl 39 and 49. Max pet at lvl 39 hits for 42 and at 49 it hits for 58.<br>
<br>
If mob has only 1/4 of his health and you kill pet/summon new one, IF new pet finishes mob then it'd be the same if pet killed mob by itself therefore it gets 50% of exp. If you let pet kill mob, then use /pet get lost then if you want all the exp YOU must finish mob, not another pet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxanthisantillias.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xanthis Antillias</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(11/25/01 1:58:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=325.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Chain casting, XP, focus items and &quot;best&quot; pet</span><hr size=1> Looks like I will have to find out what my pets hit for max at specific levels now, because a soloing mage isnt gonna have ppl around all the time to ask &quot;Hey what does this con to you?&quot;. But thanks for the info, it did nicely answering questions that I already had the answers to, but needed verification on <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubarielofluclin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bariel of Luclin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(11/25/01 4:54:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=325.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Chain casting, XP, focus items and &quot;best&quot; pet</span><hr size=1> If you look under the Pets section on this site, they have a nice list of all pets and their maximum hps, damage, etc..<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Bariel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufandarian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fandarian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/01 9:50:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=325.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Chain casting, XP, focus items and &quot;best&quot; pet</span><hr size=1> When I'm getting ready to solo (when having a low pet or a high one can mean life or death), I sic it on a nice easy green, and watch the highest hit.  At my level (30), I won't take a pet that hits less than 24.  <br>
<br>
This site has a pet statistic table.  Use it.  You don't need the highest level pet, but the lowest one against a blue mob means you're gonna go oom.  And a high blue could get you killed.<br>
<br>
Personally, I recast until I get a middle or higher pet.  Usually I can get one in about 2 or 3 casts.<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
