&quot;The Keepers&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujochangaladar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#333333>(11/30/01 4:30:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=325.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Chain casting, XP, focus items and &quot;best&quot; pet</span><hr size=1>    If you are chain casting, then the level of the pet is inconsequential, as you know the pet is going to die, and you will be replacing him.<br>
<br>
    If you are a skilled mage and you are not using chain casting as the primary tactic, you know that you may have to recast the pet anyway to avoid being without a pet, and once again if the pet hits for a couple more points or not is relatively inconsequential, especially if you are tanking for your pet a lot, and thus doing a lot of personal fire shield damage.<br>
<br>
    In my experience, a high-conning pet is only truly essential/noticeable below level 16, but even then I didn't place a lot of focus on it.  I relied more on tactics than power (though, to be honest, my tactics at that level sucked), and died a lot learning the ropes.  I started a new mage on a different server to see if it would be any easier the second time around, and it is.  If only I knew then what I know now.....<br>
<br>
Jochan Galadar, 55th magician of the Tribunal server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=larney>Larney</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(12/4/01 9:10:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=325.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gamelinx.com/everquest/eqlarney.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Chain casting, XP, focus items and &quot;best&quot; pet</span><hr size=1> With regard to recognizing your pet's level after 20, I go with the following assumption for blue cons:<br>
<br>
Only one or two levels beneath you:<br>
  &quot;It looks kind of dangerous&quot;<br>
<br>
Three or four levels beneath you:<br>
  &quot;It looks...yadda yadda... but it might be worth a try.&quot;<br>
<br>
I paraphrased, but basically you want a &quot;dangerous&quot; pet over one of those &quot;worth a try&quot; pets. Another way to tell is by how much their maximum damage is per hit. I'm at level 22 now, and my best dangerous pet maxes out at 22 hps per blow. <p><BR>
